Rating: 4
My two sisters and I just returned from a week long stay in Tuscany, Italy. We enjoyed caprese (tomatoes, mozzarella cheese and balsamic vinegar with olive oil) pretty much at every lunch and dinner. The cheese must be the very fresh, very white, soft variety. This recipe beats every tasting we had. My gourmet dining group of 88 will be serving this as a first course in eight different homes this fall. Our main course will be grilled veal chops, mashed potatoes with rosemary butter and asparagus. Do try if you haven't. You'll be delighted and so will your guests.

